style=3D"text-decoration:underline;color:#d40000;">called</a> her =E2=80=9C=
an atrocious nominee who deserves to be defeated.=E2=80=9D</li><li aria-lev=
el=3D"1" style=3D"Margin:0 0 24px 0;"><em>Searching for Bobby Kennedy</em>:=
 <strong>Robert F. Kennedy Jr.</strong>=E2=80=99s confirmation hearing for =
Health and Human Services secretary will also be this week. In the
meantime, H.H.S. has already essentially ground to a halt, ceasing communic=
ations and canceling research grant reviews at N.I.H. until political appoi=
ntees can assess it all.=C2=A0<br/><br/>Kennedy=E2=80=99s appointment has c=
aused plenty of trepidation in Washington, but his confirmation doesn=E2=80=
=99t seem to be in doubt. Trump has told him he=E2=80=99ll have carte blanc=
he to =E2=80=9Cgo wild=E2=80=9D on health as long as he doesn=E2=80=99t int=
erfere with energy production. I=E2=80=99m also told that Kennedy has assur=
ed anti-abortion senators that he
won=E2=80=99t impose his pro-choice views on health policy, and he has step=
ped away from some of the anti-vaccine organizations that paid him for lega=
l and other work on their behalf. Regardless, his hearing should be very en=
tertaining.=C2=A0</li><li aria-level=3D"1" style=3D"Margin:0 0 24px 0;"><em=
>What about those watchdogs?</em>: Trump=E2=80=99s decision to fire at leas=
t 17 agency inspectors general=E2=80=94independent agency watchdogs=E2=80=
=94in what <em>The Washington Post</em>=E2=80=99s <strong>Ruth Marcus</stro=
ng> is
calling the Friday Night Massacre, has sent shockwaves through federal agen=
cies and good governance groups. Even Senator<strong> Lindsey Graham</stron=
g>, not exactly an anti-Trump firebrand, said on <em>Meet the Press </em>th=
at Trump =E2=80=9Ctechnically=E2=80=9D violated the law by not giving Congr=
ess 30 days=E2=80=99 notice.<br/><br/>Congress is often very protective of =
inspectors general. Less than two weeks ago, Senator<strong> Joni Ernst</st=
rong> created a bipartisan inspector general caucus to =E2=80=9Cempower exe=
cutive
branch watchdogs to find ways to eliminate waste and make government more e=
fficient.=E2=80=9D Ernst has already been through it with MAGA world after =
inciting their ire for her publicly expressed concerns about Hegseth to lea=
d the Defense Department. (Ernst=E2=80=99s office sent me a cautious statem=
ent in reaction to the firings: =E2=80=9CSenator Ernst looks forward to lea=
rning more about this decision and working with the president to nominate r=
eplacements, so the important work of independent investigators to root
out waste, fraud, and abuse can continue with full transparency.=E2=80=9D) =
Senators <strong>Chuck Grassley</strong> and <strong>James Lankford</strong=
> are the two other Republicans in that bipartisan group. But we=E2=80=99ll=
 see if there=E2=80=99s any real pushback.</li></ul></div>
