9999999997px;"><strong>Rioters,
What Rioters?</strong></h3>
</td></tr></tbody></table>
<table width=3D"100%" border=3D"0" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" role=
=3D"presentation" style=3D"mso-table-lspace:0pt;mso-table-rspace:0pt;word-b=
reak:break-word;"><tbody><tr><td style=3D"padding-bottom:32px;"><div style=
=3D"color:#000000;direction:ltr;font-family:&#39;Inter&#39;,&#39;Arial&#39;=
;font-size:17px;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:0px;line-height:150%;text-al=
ign:left;mso-line-height-alt:25.5px;"><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0p=
x;">Far more so than during Trump=E2=80=99s first term, these lawmakers are=
 largely shaking off the
stuff they don=E2=80=99t like. Most of my top Republican sources confided t=
hat they were frustrated at Trump=E2=80=99s pardoning of violent January 6 =
rioters, but many justified the maneuver by both-sidesing the issue=E2=80=
=94pointing to Biden=E2=80=99s preemptive pardons of his family, or his com=
mutation of <strong>Leonard Peltier</strong>, the 80-year-old Native Americ=
an activist convicted of killing two F.B.I. agents in 1977. Others also pri=
vately admitted that they remain uneasy about his plan to alter the meaning=
 of the
14th Amendment on birthright citizenship and his extrajudicial disregard fo=
r the TikTok ban, but they are keeping those unpleasant thoughts mostly to =
themselves.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p =
style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">Alas, profiles in courage have been r=
eplaced by an abundance of opportunism. For so many on the right=E2=80=94se=
emingly <em>everyone</em>, really=E2=80=94the reality is there=E2=80=99s to=
o much upside to cause an uproar over any of these thorny or highly
controversial topics. Trump=E2=80=99s ability to <em>flood the zone</em>, t=
he hokey bit of D.C. argot for unleashing a flurry of activity to discombob=
ulate his foes and inoculate his various agenda topics from critique, has a=
lso rendered their potential fulminations inert. The chaos and freneticism =
that was seen as <em>unpredictable</em> or <em>unprecedented </em>during hi=
s first term=E2=80=94and I=E2=80=99m just cherry-picking some typical media=
 adjectives=E2=80=94is all entirely predictable now, and lawmakers are neit=
her
surprised nor confused. They=E2=80=99re just going with the flow.=C2=A0</p>=
<p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;mar=
gin-bottom:0px;">And yet, the other element of <em>flooding the zone</em> i=
s that Republican lawmakers are now underwater, buried under a deluge of wo=
rk. On top of starting a new Congress and confirming Trump=E2=80=99s cabine=
t, they=E2=80=99re sorting through the flurry of executive orders and other=
 first-week actions.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=
=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;"><em>Unity, unity, unity</em> is th=
e mantra among Republicans=E2=80=94often uttered with a knowing eye roll. P=
rivately, Republicans acknowledge that the Trump honeymoon will be short. S=
enate Republicans are already pointing fingers at House Republicans for mak=
ing the process of <em>how </em>to pass Trump=E2=80=99s agenda overly compl=
icated=E2=80=94there are a lot of<strong> Joe Manchin</strong> wannabes in =
the House, one Senate aide told me, suggesting that attention-hound members
will seek fame by blocking Congress=E2=80=99s work. In other words, despite=
 the public posturing, the House G.O.P.=E2=80=99s disparate ideological fac=
tions are setting up their battle stations.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;m=
argin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;">Rep. <strong>Mike Lawle=
r</strong> of New York organized a meeting with Trump for himself and the o=
nly two other Republicans who represent districts <strong>Kamala Harris </s=
trong>won=E2=80=94Reps. <strong>Brian Fitzpatrick</strong> and <strong>Don
Bacon</strong>. It was short, I was told, and Lawler talked about the need =
to increase the SALT deduction, while Bacon focused on issues important to =
Omaha. In any event, the meeting was mainly about getting face time with a =
president and reminding him that they=E2=80=99re in tough districts that ar=
e vastly different from the deep red districts of many of their more vocal =
and obstinate colleagues.=C2=A0</p></div>
</td></tr></tbody></table>
